Novell appoints Ronald W. Hovsepian as President, North America | Micro Focus







































 







Novell appoints Ronald W. Hovsepian as President, North America
Proven IBM executive brings extensive and diverse general management expertise in IT solutions strategy, sales, marketing and business development 
Will lead all sales and marketing activity in Novell's North America territory
3 June 2003



Novell announced today that Ronald W. Hovsepian has been appointed president, North America, effective immediately. In this role, he will be responsible for leading all aspects of Novell's operations in its North America business unit and will become a member of the company's worldwide management committee. He will report to Jack L. Messman, chairman, president and chief executive officer of Novell, Inc. Hovsepian assumes the position held by H. Carvel Moore, who has left the company.
A veteran of twenty years in the technology sector, Hovsepian, 42, has significant experience leading sales and marketing organizations focused on delivering IT solutions for enterprises across a wide spectrum of industries, including retail, consumer packaged goods and wholesale. He spent more than seventeen years at IBM Corporation, including three years as worldwide general manager of Industry Solutions in the retail sector from 1998 - 2001. With stints in various sales and marketing positions prior to taking profit and loss responsibility at several IBM units, he brings a proven track record of achieving revenue goals and profit growth in the IT solutions business. More recently, he was managing an investment team overseeing the top 30 investments for the Internet Capital Group (ICG), serving on the senior executive team for investments, and working directly with many of the companies in which ICG invested to help them grow.
"Today Novell has significantly added to its management team and our ability to deliver business solutions for our customers," said Messman. "Ron brings broad and deep solutions sales and marketing experience in the technology sector, as well as an in-depth understanding of the IT market and what customers are looking for today. Having helped customers benefit from solutions before, Ron can now use those skills to provide Novell's customers with the secure identity management, web-based application development, and cross-platform networking solutions they are looking for."
At IBM, Hovsepian held various sales, marketing and managerial positions, including director of Consumer Driven Solutions and vice president, Global Supply Chain Solutions, prior to his role as worldwide general manager of Industry Solutions. Following that, he served as managing director, Operations, at Internet Capital Group. He is currently a member of the board of directors of the Ann Taylor Corporation.
Hovsepian received a Bachelor of Science degree in Marketing from Boston College. He resides in Holliston, Massachusetts, with his wife and their four children.


About Novell
Novell, Inc. (Nasdaq: NOVL) delivers Software for the Open Enterprise™. With more than 50,000 customers in 43 countries, Novell helps customers manage, simplify, secure and integrate their technology environments by leveraging best-of-breed, open standards-based software. With over 20 years of experience, more than 5,000 employees, 5,000 partners and support centers around the world, Novell helps customers gain control over their IT operating environment while reducing cost. More information about Novell can be found at http://www.novell.com.

Novell is a registered trademarks; Nsure, exteNd and Nteprise are trademarks; and Ngage is a service mark of Novell, Inc. in the United States and other countries. * All third-party trademarks are the property of their respective owners.

















